                <p><strong>Welcome to Nelya!</strong></p><p><strong>Nelya is owned and operated by Apprecano Ltd.</strong></p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\">We designed this privacy policy to inform you about our practices regarding the collection, storage, processing and protection of personal data. At Nelya, we deeply value the privacy and security of our users, so the application has been designed to work without an Internet connection and without the need for an account, ensuring that all your information remains on your device.</p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\"> </p><p><strong>1.ABSENCE OF DATA COLLECTION AND PROCESSING</strong></p><p>Nelya is an application that works completely locally on your device. This means that:</p><ul><li>We do not collect, store or share any personal data, whether it is identifying information, contact data or sensitive health data.</li><li>We do not have access to any data entered in the application.</li><li>We do not process any data on servers, cloud storage or external databases.</li><li>We do not allow third party access to any user information, as all information remains strictly on the user's device.</li></ul><p class=\"ql-align-justify\">This implies that any information you enter in the application is your sole responsibility. Nelya has no ability to recover, restore or transfer information in the event of loss or damage to the device.</p><p> </p><p><strong>2. COMPLIANCE WITH PRIVACY REGULATIONS</strong></p><p>Since Nelya does not collect or process any personal information, we are not subject to international data protection regulations, such as:</p><ul><li><strong>General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) </strong>of the European Union, which regulates the processing of personal data within the EU and the EEA.</li><li><strong>California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA)</strong>, which grants privacy rights to California residents.</li><li><strong>Health Insurance Portability and Accountability Act (HIPAA)</strong>, which regulates